	    girls says. ~We need all the space we can get.~";
	],
 has 	scenery pluralname;

Object 	-> second_bedroom_tiles "tiles"
 with 	name
	    'tile' 'tiles' 'game' 'board' 'roads' 'road' 'castles'
	    'castle' 'landscape' 'circle' 'circles' 'gap' 'gaps' 'map',
	description
	[;
	    print_ret (The) self, " depict little roads and castles 
		and things -- together, they form a weird sort of 
		pseudo-medieval landscape. Except there are a couple 
		of roads that just run in circles, and there are odd 
		little gaps in the map.";
	],
	before
	[;
	 Take, Push:
	    "~Hey!~ says one of the girls. ~Don't touch that. That's
	    our city.~";

	 Play:
	    "You're not really clear on how to play.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object -> second_bedroom_girls "girls"
 with	name
	    'girls' 'girl' 'mysterious' 'alice' 'alicia'
	    'handkerchief' 'handkerchiefs' 'shirts' 't//' 't-shirts'
	    't-shirt' 'shirt' 'jeans',
	description
	    "The girls are difficult to regard individually. Your 
	    eyes just slide from one to the other naturally. They're 
	    both maybe seventeen if you're generous, with black hair 
	    they've got done up in matching red handkerchiefs. 
	    T-shirts and jeans, of course -- you're not sure exactly 
	    how to classify these two beyond, of course, Too Young 
	    for A Roll in the Hay But Lest We Not Forget Our 
	    Purpose, Probably Old Enough to Drive.",
	before
	[;
	 AskForRide:
	    self.number++;
	    print_ret "~Hey, is there any chance either of you could 
		give me a ride? It's real important,~ you say.^^",
		(The) self, " look up at you, almost simultaneously, 
		almost enough to freak you out.^^~We can't go,~ one 
		says. ~We really have to stay until the game is 
		over.~";

	 Play:
	    <<Play second_bedroom_tiles>>;
	],
	react_before
	[;
	 Go:
	    if ((noun == s_obj) && (silver_key in self) &&
		(self.number > 2))
	    {
	    	move silver_key to player;
	    	print_ret "~Wait,~ one of ", (the) self, " says. 
		    ~You'll need this.~^^She holds open her hand: 
		    there's a silver key resting there. ~Take it,~ 
		    she says. ~It won't open any doors for you, but 
		    it'll be useful.~^^You pocket it... who can turn 
		    down a useful key?";
	    };
	],
	react_after
	[;
	 Enter:
	    if (noun == second_bedroom_bed)
		print_ret "One of ", (the) self, " gives you a 
		    suspicious look as you climb onto the bed.";
	],
	life
	[;
	 Attack:
	    "But why, dude?";

	 Kiss:
	    "Come on, man. You're twenty-three years old. These kids 
	    are probably in high school or something. That ain't 
	    right.";

	 Give:
	    if (noun == silver_key)
		print_ret "~It's for you,~ one of ", (the) self, " 
		    says.";
	    else
	    	print_ret "~No thanks,~ one of ", (the) self, " 
		    says. ~We have to put everything we have out on 
		    the table, so we don't want more stuff.~";

	 Show:
	    if (noun == silver_key)
		print_ret "One of ", (the) self, " nods at you 
		    encouragingly.";
	    else
	    	"They don't seem too impressed.";

	 Answer:
	    print_ret (The) self, " look at you blankly.";
	    
	 Ask:
	    switch (second)
	    {
	     'ride', 'car':
		<<AskForRide self>>;
		
	     'girl', 'girls', 'herself', 'themselves':
		self.number++;
		"~So what are a pair of girls like you doing here?~
		you ask.^^~We've been here since yesterday,~ one
		replies. ~This is important work.~^^~I'm getting a
		masters,~ the other says, sort of absently.";

	     'masters', 'master', 'degree':
		self.number++;
		"~What are you studying?~^^~SimCity,~ she
		says.^^~Civil fallacies,~ the other corrects.";

	     'civil', 'fallacies':
		self.number++;
		"~What the hell kind of field of study is civil
		fallacies?~ you ask.^^~Civil what? I'm studying
		ergodic literature,~ the girl says.";

	     'ergodic', 'literature':
		self.number++;
		"~What's ergodic literature?~^^~It's stories with
		paths,~ the girl explains. ~It's great because I can
		read anything I want to, because every story has a
		path.~ She looks at you for a moment, then adds: ~You
		have a path too, you know.~";

	     'path', 'paths':
		self.number++;
		"~What path am I on?~ you ask.^^~Same as we are,~
		one girl says. ~We'll tell you more the next time we
		see you.~";
		
	     'rules', 'playing':
		self.number++;
		"~How do you play this game?~ you ask, indicating the
		tables.^^~The rules are secret,~ one of the girls
		says. ~At least for you, they are.~";
		
	     'tile', 'tiles', 'game', 'city':
		self.number++;
		"~Excuse me if I'm being kind of rude here, but what
		are you guys doing?~ you ask.^^~We're playing
		Carcassonne,~ the girl nearest you says. ~We're
		building a city.~^^~Soon it's going to be big enough
		to have its own airport and ice cream factory,~ the
		other girl explains.";

	     'play', 'playing':
		self.number++;
		"~Hey, can I play?~ you ask.^^~Sorry,~ one girl
		says. ~It's really delicate. One wrong move and the
		whole thing will collapse.~^^~Don't take it
		personally,~ the other girl says. ~You seem nice,
		maybe even brave, but it's for the best. You don't
		have time to play games, do you?~";
		
	     'table', 'tables':
		self.number++;
		"~Where'd you get all these tables from?~ you
		ask.^^They look up at you. ~There's a lot of tables in
		the world, if you just stop to notice,~ one says.";

	     'carcassonne':
		self.number++;
		"~What the fuck is Carcassonne?~ you ask.^^~It's 
		like a city in France or something,~ one of the 
		girls says. ~But we're making a better version now.~";

	     'airport':
		self.number++;
		"~Where are you putting the airport?~ you ask.^^~Next
		to the public library,~ one of them replies drily.";

	     'public', 'library':
		self.number++;
		"~Where's the library?~ you ask. One of them just
		rolls her eyes at you.";
		
	     'ice', 'cream', 'factory':
		self.number++;
		print_ret "~What now about the ice cream factory?~ 
		    you ask.^^~You've never been to one?~ one of ",
		    (the) self, " asks.^^~Nope.~^^~You should go,~ 
		    she says. ~We went up the East Coast on a road 
		    trip, checking them all out, until we got to 
		    Vermont, where Ben and Jerry's main one is.~ She 
		    looks at you, maybe assessing something. ~You 
		    look like a trip would do you good.~";

	     'drugs', 'drug', 'green', 'cough', 'syrup', 'dxm',
	     'absinthe':
		self.number++;
		print_ret "~Hey, do you guys know anything about... 
		    say, a green liquid you drink that probably is 
		    some form of drug?~^^~No, but I expect you 
		    might,~ one of ", (the) self, " says.";

	     'beer', 'beers':
		self.number++;
		print_ret "~Can I get you a beer?~ you ask.^^~No 
		    thanks,~ one of ", (the) self, " says, giving 
		    you an irritated look. ~We don't drink.~";

	     'wine', 'yellow', 'pumpkin':
		self.number++;
		if (wine_bottle notin post_attic_darkness)
		    print_ret "~Do you guys know where I could find 
			some wine?~ you ask.^^~No...~ one of ",
			(the) self, " replies.";
		else
		    print_ret "~Do you guys know what's up with this 
			wine I found in the attic?~ you ask.^^One of 
			", (the) self, " gives it a quick once-over. 
			~Doesn't look familiar,~ she says.";
		
	     'party', 'house', 'here', 'dance', 'dancing':
		self.number++;
		"~Why aren't you guys downstairs with everyone else?~
		you ask.^^~We don't like people as much as we do
		places,~ one girl says. ~No offense.~";

	     'cloister':
		self.number++;
		"~What's a cloister?~ you ask.^^~It's like a church,~
		one girl replies. ~Except smaller, with monks and
		things inside.~";
		
	     'sue':
		self.number++;
		"~I'm trying to find someone named Sue,~ you
		explain.^^~We don't really meet people,~ one girl
		says.";

	     'wanda':
		self.number++;
		print "~Do you know anyone named Wanda?~ you
		    ask.^^~Sorry,~ a girl says. ~Wanda's a pretty
		    name, though. It's the kind of name only people
		    in novels have because it's too pretty for
		    someone to have all their life.~";

		if (self.name_talked)
		    "^^~Didn't you already say that?~ the other girl
		    asks.^^~Maybe. I have trouble remembering my own
		    name sometimes.~";
		else
		{
		    self.name_talked = true;
		    print_ret " ";
		};

	     'silver', 'key', 'alice', 'alicia':
		if (silver_key notin self)
		    "~What's the story on this key?~ you ask.^^They
		    just smile enigmatically.";
		else
		    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
		
	     default:
		"The two girls look at you briefly, decide not to 
		answer.";
	    };

	 Tell:
	    switch (second)
	    {
	     'myself':
		self.number++;
		"~My name's Dante,~ you say.^^~Hi,~ a girl says. ~My
		name's Alice, and hers is Alicia.~^^Of course you
		immediately forget which is which. Dammit. You suck at
		remembering names.";

	     'drugs', 'drug', 'green', 'cough', 'syrup', 'dxm',
	     'absinthe':
		self.number++;
		"~Just as an FYI,~ you say, ~I'm on drugs and you two
		are kind of freaking me out.~^^~I know,~ one girl
		says. ~We don't mean to. We just have a mission.~^^~It
		must be nice,~ you say.";

	     'wine':
		if (wine_bottle notin post_attic_darkness)
		{
		    self.number++;
		    print_ret "~Hey, I found this weird wine up in 
			the attic,~ you say.^^~Oh yeah?~ one of ",
			(the) self, " asks, vaguely trying to sound 
			interested.";
		};
		
	     'beatrice':
		self.number++;
		print "~There's this girl I know who I think is in
		    trouble,~ you say.^^~What's her name?~ one girl
		    asks as she places a tile on a
		    table.^^~Beatrice.~^^~It's a pretty name,~ she
		    says. ~It's the kind of name only people in novels
		    have because it's too pretty for someone to have
		    all their life.~";

		if (self.name_talked)
		    "^^~You said that already, I think,~ the other 
		    girl says.^^~I know, but I like it when I say 
		    things that are true.~";
		else
		{
		    self.name_talked = true;
		    print_ret " ";
		};

	     default:
		<<Ask self 'uh'>>;
	    };
	],
	each_turn
	[;
	    if (random(3) == 1)
	    {
		switch (random(13))
		{
		 1, 2:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " pauses for a 
			moment, murmurs a couple words to herself, 
			and places a tile down.^^~That's 
			interesting,~ the other says.";

		 2, 3, 4:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " picks up a 
			tile and holds it to her lips, thinking it 
			over.";

		 5:
		    "^~Are you trying to screw up my cloister?~ one
		    girl asks.";

		 6:
		    print_ret "^~I forgot whose turn it is,~ one of ",
			(the) self, " says.^^~It's yours, of 
			course,~ the other replies.";

		 7:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " drops a tile 
			by accident, and swipes it up as fast as she 
			can.";

		 8:
		    print_ret "^~You shouldn't put that there,~ one of
			", (the) self, " comments. ~You're never 
			going to be able to finish that castle.~";

		 9, 10, 11:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " hands a tile 
			to the other.";

		 12:
		    print_ret "^~Twenty-three points,~ one of ", (the)
			self, " notes.";

		 13:
		    print_ret "^~You can't put that there,~ one of ",
			(the) self, " says. ~The wall doesn't 
			match.~";
		};
	    };
	],
	orders
	[;
	    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
	],
	name_talked false,
	number 0,
 has 	animate pluralname female concealed;

Object 	-> -> silver_key "silver key"
 with 	name
	    'silver' 'key',
	description
	[;
	    if (party_alice.has_appeared)
	    	aliced.sync_belief();
	    
	    print_ret "It's a small key, with the name ", (string)
		aliced.capped_name(), " inscribed in it. Hmm.";
	];

!
! First floor
!

Class FridgeBeer
 with short_name
	[;
	    if (self hasnt general)
	    {
		if (self in kitchen_fridge)
		    print "beer in the fridge";
		else
		    print "beer";
	    }
	    else
	       	print "empty bottle of beer";
	    return true;
	],
	parse_name
	[ i word;
	    if (parser_action == ##TheSame)
	    {
		! we are comparing two FridgeBeers
		
	     	if (((parser_one hasnt general) && (parser_two hasnt
						    general))
		    || ((parser_one has general) && (parser_two has
						     general)))
		    return -1;
		else
		    return -2;
	    }
	    else
	    	while (true)
	    	{
		    ! we are parsing words -- allowing 'empty'
		    ! to refer to empty bottles
		    
	       	    word = NextWord();
		    
		    if (word == 'empty')
		    	if (self has general)
		    	    i++;
		    	else
		    	    return i;
		    else
		    	if (word == 'glass' or 'bottle' or 'beer')
		    	    i++;
		    	else
			    if (word == 'bottles' or 'beers')
			    {
			    	i++;
			    	parser_action = ##PluralFound;
			    }
			    else
			    	return i;
	    	};
	],
	plural
	[;
	    if (self hasnt general)
	    	print "beers";
	    else
		print "empty beer bottles";
	],
	description
	[;
	    if (self hasnt general)
	    	"It's probably for the best that these beers are
		left ambiguous. You're a level 1 beer snob, which
		means you're smart enough to know that most any beer
		you're likely to discover at a party would be
		considered a crime against nature by any
		right-thinking human being... but just as you have
		to shrug your shoulders when the DJ cranks up ~Hit
		Me Baby, One More Time,~ so too must sacrifices be
		made when it comes to alcohol.^^(Besides which, why
		start worrying about what you're throwing down your
		gullet now?)";
	    else
		"Eh, your average empty glass bottle. You've never
		been in a bar brawl before, but holding an empty by
		the neck always give you a weird sense of security.";
	],
	before
	[;
	 Take:
	    if (self.dont_take)
		"Hey, if three beers were good enough for Douglas
		Adams, they ought to be good enough for you.";
	    
	 Drink:
	    if (self hasnt general)
	    {
		give self general;
	    	player.beers++;
	    	print "No poison like the present. It tastes kind
		    of... ";
	    	print (string) random("chocolate-y", "like muskrat",
				  "terrible");
	    	print "? But really, thinking about what it's doing 
		    to your taste buds is missing the point";
		if (player.beers == 1)
		    ". You feel different -- in a different kind of
		    way than before. You aren't as worried, not as
		    rushed: you're looser, if you need a word to
		    describe it.";
		else
		    ".";
	    }
	    else
		"Actually, captain, it looks like this bottle's
		empty.";

	 Open:
	    if (self hasnt open)
	    {
		give self open;
		print_ret "You open the bottle of ", (name) self, ". 
		    Ah, the wonder and majesty of twist-offs.";
	    }
	    else
		"It's already open.";

	 Close:
	    if (self hasnt open)
		"You haven't opened it yet.";
	    else
		"Bah, screw saving it for later.";

	 ThrowAt:
	    "Hey, let's not get destructive here.";
	],
	dont_take
            false;

Class 	PreDanceRoom
 with 	react_before
	[;
	 Ask, Tell, Answer:
	    "It's much too loud to talk.";
	],
	before
	[;
	 Dance:
	    print "Okay. Time to give it a shot.^^";
	    
	    if (player.drank_wine)
	    {
		print "Finally. Finally you can do it right, for 
		    once in your life. Finally there's no awkward 
		    feeling, no weird suspicion that someone is 
		    watching you, taking notes even, chuckling to 
		    themselves about how uncoordinated you are, how 
		    you are so terribly white, how you don't belong, 
		    how you ought to go home and catch up on your 
		    email, maybe even re-do your desktop wallpaper 
		    while you're at it, then pop onto Instant 
		    Messenger and pretend to have a 
		    conversation.^^No one can say anything to you 
		    now.^";
	    	PlayerTo(dancing_dance);
		rtrue;
	    };
	    
	    if (player.beers > 0)
	    {
		print "Something deep in your stomach goes into 
		    action -- you'd like to imagine that it's 
		    something fundamentally cool, buried deep down 
		    inside your body. But let's be honest. It isn't 
		    anything cool. All the beer ever did for you is 
		    stop you from thinking you're an idiot.^^But 
		    what the fuck. It's good enough.^";
 		PlayerTo(dancing_dance);
		rtrue;
	    }
	    else
		"You've always considered yourself a good dancer, at 
		least as geeks go. But this one is a little beyond 
		your current capabilities. There are just too many 
		beats to try to synchronize your hips to, and it's 
		no use trying to follow anyone else's moves. They 
		all keep changing their rhythm.^^There's gotta be a 
		solution to this problem. There always is.";

	 Sing:
	    "The words of the music come too quickly, too 
	    confusingly for you to try to follow along.";
	];

Class 	PreDanceObject
 with 	found_in
	[;
	    return (location ofclass PreDanceRoom);
	],
 has 	scenery;

PartyRoom foyer "In A Foyer, Among the Stoners"
 with 	description
	[;
	    print "The music is incredibly loud, booming even, but
		that hasn't stopped some fucking stoners, too
		unmotivated to even get up and dance, from watching
		Dr. Who on the old TV set sitting against one wall.
		They're all slumped in different positions on an
		orange couch, staring idly at the newest adventures
		of a British dude in space.^^To the west is what
		used to be the living room but is now a solid mass
		of people dancing, grooving, groping";

	    if (center_dance has visited)
		print " -- but through all that chaff, you can now
		    see the guy at the center clearly. In a word,
		    he's lost.";
    	    else
		print ". They've set up one of those budget
		    disco-ball projectors and because of it, you
		    can't distinguish people at all in there. It's
		    all just once big dance. The weird part is that
		    it looks like there's a pole in the middle of
		    the whole thing. What's the story on that?";

	    SetPronoun('them', foyer_stoners);
	    "^^The front door's to the south, and the kitchen --
	    which for some reason appears to be empty -- is north.";
	],
	w_to
	[;
	    if (center_dance hasnt visited)
		return edge_of_dance;
	    else
	    {
		print "It's so easy to go places when you know where
		    they are -- and that weird sound, that soft happy
		    sound, the one you had heard before is back and
		    the music is gone.^";
		return center_dance;
	    };
	],
	u_to second_landing,
	n_to kitchen,
	s_to foyer_door,
	out_to
	[;
	    <<Go s_obj>>;
	];

Object 	-> foyer_door "front door"
 with 	name
	    'front' 'door' 'off' 'white',
	describe
	[;
	    rtrue;
	],
	description
	    "It's the same off-white almost every house-for-rent
	    you've been to has -- you've been to paint stores, you
	    know there are tons of kinds of off-white, but they all
	    seem to have exactly the same one.",
	door_dir s_to,
	door_to front_porch,
 has 	static door openable;

Object 	-> foyer_tv "television set"
 with 	name
	    'tv' 'television' 'set' 'dr' 'doctor' 'who' 'british'
	    'dude' 'screen',
	description
	    "This week, it looks like Dr. Who's chilling in a 
	    British army base, and if you are actually seeing what 
	    you're seeing, he is engaged in a drinking contest with 
	    either a robot or a crystalline alien. What the fuck. Do 
	    they even have any concept of national security over 
	    there?",
	before
	[;
	 Take:
	    print_ret (The) self, "'s a little too heavy to be 
		toting around.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> foyer_couch "orange couch"
 with 	name
	    'couch' 'orange',
	description
	    "It's just this couch, you know?",
	before
	[;
	 Take:
	    "The stoners are kind of using it right now.";

	 Enter:
	    "There's no room, man.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

FarScenery -> foyer_dance "people dancing"
 with 	name
	    'people' 'dancing' 'dance' 'mass' 'crowd',
	description
	    "It's hard to make people from all the arms waving and --
	    it's just like watching anenomes in an aquarium.",
 has 	animate pluralname;

FarScenery -> foyer_pole
 with	short_name
	[;
   	    if (center_dance has visited)
		print "guy at the center of the crowd";
	    else
		print "dark pole shape";
	    rtrue;
	],
	parse_name
	[ i;
	   while (true)
	   {
	      switch (NextWord())
	      {
	       'dark', 'pole':
		  if (center_dance hasnt visited)
		      i++;
		  else
		      return i;

	       'guy', 'chris', 'man', 'dude', 'center':
		  if (center_dance has visited)
		      i++;
		  else
		      return i;
		  
	       default:
		  return i;
	      };
	   };
	],
	description
	[;
	    if (center_dance hasnt visited)
	    	"You can't make out anything from here beyond the
		shape.";
	    else
		"He's just an ordinary guy. What's he doing there?";
	];

Object 	-> foyer_stoners "stoners"
 with 	name
	    'stoner' 'stoners' 'guys' 'guy' 'left' 'middle' 'right'
	    'smart' 'one',
	description
	    "The three guys parked on the couch may actually be
	    perfectly average young men. It's just a gut feeling
	    here that they smoke weed on a regular basis. Maybe it's
	    the corduroy pants they're wearing or something. You've
	    never trusted anyone wearing corduroy pants.",
	life
	[;
	 Answer:
	    "The one in the middle looks at you for a second, then
	    says, ~Well alright, if you say so, man.~";

	 Kiss:
	    "As interesting as things might turn out if you did
	    that... let's keep your pothead love on the DL for now.";

	 Attack:
	    print_ret "Going after some peaceful ", (name) self, " 
		stoners? Come on.";

	 Give:
	    if (noun == drug_bottle)
		<<Show drug_bottle self>>;
	    "~No thanks,~ the one on the left says.";

	 Show:
	    if (noun == drug_bottle)
		"~Hey, what do you make of this?~ you ask, showing
		them the bottle.^^~Hunh,~ the one on the right
		says. ~Looks like a plain old cough syrup bottle to
		me.~";
	    "They don't look terribly amazed.";

	 Ask:
	    switch (second)
	    {
	     'ride', 'car':
		<<AskForRide self>>;

	     'dr', 'who', 'television', 'tv', 'episode', 'drinking',
	     'contest':
		"~What's this episode you're watching?~ you ask.^^~I
		dunno, man,~ one of them comments. ~I think, like, the
		universe is going to blow up if Dr. Who can't hold his
		liquor.~^^~Doesn't he have six livers or something?~
		another comments.";
		
	     'themselves', 'himself', 'stoners':
		"~Who are you guys, anyway?~ you ask.^^~Right now,
		we're sitting on this couch,~ the one in the middle
		says.^^~No, you dumbass,~ the one on his left says.
		~He asked who we are.~^^~Oh,~ the other one replies.
		~Well, that's a story too long to be told.~";

	     'drug', 'drugs', 'green', 'liquid', 'cough', 'syrup',
	     'bottle':
		self.number++;
		print "~Hey, I just drank this weird green liquid 
		    and I have no idea what it was... any thoughts?~ 
		    you say.^^~Hmm, could be absinthe,~ one of the 
		    stoners says.^^~I doubt it,~ another says. ~They 
		    don't make it strong enough these days. How hard 
		    are you tripping?~^^~Let me get back to you on 
		    that one,~ you reply.^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;

	     'party', 'house', 'dancing', 'dance', 'people':
		"~So I guess you guys aren't too impressed by the
		party,~ you say.^^~Nah, man. It started out awesome,
		but then it turned into this fucking rave, and we
		are many things, but ravers we are not,~ the one on
		the right says, gesturing over at the living
		room.^^~Drunk ravers especially,~ the one on the
		left says.";

	     'pole':
		"~What's up with that pole in the living room?~ you
		ask. ~I don't remember it being there before.^^~Dude,
		I don't the fucking foggiest,~ one of the stoners
		says. ~What they're doing over there is probably
		illegal in some state of mind or something.~";

	     'pholcodine':
		self.number++;
		print "~Do you guys know what Pholcodine is?~ you
		    ask.^^~Pholcodine? Nah, dude,~ the one with an
		    acid green T-shirt on says. ~Do you mean
		    codeine?~^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;

	     'codeine':
		self.number++;
		print "~What does codeine do to you?~ you 
		    ask.^^~Makes you happy,~ the stoner on the right 
		    says and scratches his head. ~Makes you want to 
		    go to sleep.~^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;

	     'absinthe':
		self.number++;
	     	print "~Tell me about absinthe,~ you say.^^~What, you
		    never saw ";
		style underline;
		print "Moulin Rouge";
		style roman;
		print "? It makes you see shit,~ the one on the left 
		    says.^^~Shit that isn't there,~ the stoner next 
		    to him clarifies.^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;

	     'marijuana', 'weed', 'pot', 'sensamilla':
		self.number++;
		print "~Do you guys have any weed?~ you ask.^^The 
		    one in the middle almost says something, but his 
		    buddy over on the left puts a hand on his knee 
		    and answers for him: ~We don't smoke the 
		    sensamilla.~^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;

	     'beer', 'alcohol':
		if (kitchen_fridge has general)
		{
		    print "~Do you guys want a drink?~ you ask.^^";

		    if (~~player.beers)
		    	"~Nah, man, it looks like you could use it 
			more than we could,~ the one on the left 
			says.";
		    else
		    	"~No thanks, mi amigo,~ the stoner on the 
			right says. ~We already ate.~";
		}
		else
		    "~Hey, do you know where I can get a beer around
		    here?~ you ask.^^~Well, this is a pretty big leap
		    of faith,~ the stoner in the middle says. ~But
		    have you checked the fridge yet?~";

	     'wine':
		if (wine_bottle notin post_attic_darkness)
		{
      		    self.number++;
		    print "~I found this weird bottle of orange wine 
			up in the attic,~ you say. ~Do you guys know 
			anything about it?~^^~Well, they do make 
			wine out of oranges sometimes...~ the stoner 
			on the right says.^^~They make wine out of 
			everything, man,~ the one in the middle 
			says. ~You can even make it out of fucking 
			Mountain Dew.~^";
		    self.drug_check();
		    rtrue;
		}
		else
		    "~Do you guys know if there's any wine around?~ 
		    you ask.^^~Nah, man,~ one of the stoners 
		    replies. ~But there's some beer in the fridge.~";
		
	     'dxm':
		self.number++;
		print "~Do you guys know anything about DXM?~ you 
		    ask.^^~Dextromethorphan?~ the one in the middle 
		    says. ~Nah, I've never heard of it.~^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;
		
	     'wanda':
		if (~~ self.talked_wanda)
		{
		    self.talked_wanda = true;
		    print "~What does Wanda look like?~ you 
			ask.^^~Uh, she's kind of pretty,~ one of 
			them says.^^~Nah, man, I wouldn't say she's 
			pretty, except like that girl from ";
		    style underline;
		    print "Sex in the City";
		    style roman;
		    " is pretty,~ the one in the middle 
		    comments.^^~She's about yea tall--~ the one on 
		    the right says, gesturing with his hand at about 
		    five foot two. ~And she's got an eyepatch 
		    on.~^^~Don't fuck with him,~ the middle one 
		    says. ~She doesn't have an eyepatch.~^^~Then 
		    maybe we should tell him her name's not Wanda,~ 
		    the one on the right says. ~Actually, it's Sue.~";
		}
		else
		    "~So you were just making up all that stuff 
		    about Wanda?~ you ask.^^~Yeah, I was just 
		    shitting you,~ the one on the left says. ~To 
		    tell you the truth, I'm just trying to entertain 
		    myself with some scintillating conversation. 
		    This Dr. Who episode blows.~^^~Hey, do you 
		    remember how to spell scintillating?~ the one in 
		    the middle asks.";

	     'sue':
	    	if (~~ self.talked_sue)
	    	{
		    self.talked_sue = true;
		    "~What's Sue look like?~ you ask.^^~Ah, you'd 
		    know Sue if you met her,~ the middle stoner 
		    says. ~But I'll tell you a secret. You can tell 
		    if it's the real Sue because her belly button 
		    isn't pierced.~^^~Sue would never pierce a 
		    single thing on her beautiful body,~ the one on 
		    the left says. ~She's a vegan, man.~^^~I 
		    wouldn't call her beautiful,~ the middle one 
		    retorts. ~Just kind of pretty.~^^~Oh, Jesus, 
		    don't start this argument again,~ the one on the 
		    left says.";
	    	}
	    	else
		    "~So Sue is a real and factual person,~ you 
		    say.^^~Yeah,~ the left stoner says. ~As far as I 
		    know, anyway.~";

	     default:
		"The stoners look at you and shrug. It's hard to say 
		whether this is due to an actual lack of knowledge 
		on their part, or if they just don't feel like 
		talking to you.";
	    };

	 Tell:
	    switch (second)
	    {
	     'me', 'myself':
		"~Hi, I'm Dante,~ you say.^^~Sup,~ the one on the 
		left, who appears least interested in the TV, says.";

	     'beatrice':
		if (self.asked_ride)
		    "~The reason why I'm asking for a ride is 
		    because there's this girl I know who's in really 
		    bad shape, and I need to help her,~ you 
		    explain.^^~Sorry, man,~ the one on the left 
		    says. ~We'd help you if we could.~";
		else
		    "~Hey, this girl I know is in really bad shape,~
		    you say.^^The one on the right fixes you with a
		    weird look. ~What do you want us to do about
		    it?~";
		
	     'drug', 'drugs', 'green', 'liquid', 'bottle',
	     'pholcodine':
		self.number++;
		print "~Hey, I just drank this weird green liquid 
		    and I have no idea what it was... any thoughts?~ 
		    you say.^^~Hmm, could be absinthe,~ one of the 
		    stoners says.^^~I doubt it,~ another says. ~They 
		    don't make it strong enough these days. How hard 
		    are you tripping?~^^ ~Let me get back to you on 
		    that one,~ you reply.^";
		self.drug_check();
		rtrue;
	    };
	],
	react_before
	[;
	 SwitchOn, SwitchOff:
	    if (noun == foyer_tv)
		"~Hey!~ one of the stoners says when you reach for 
		the dial. ~Watching this show is quite possibly the 
		most important thing happening to anyone anywhere
		right nowq.~";
	],
	before
	[;
	 AskForRide:
	    self.asked_ride = true;
	    "~Hey, can any of you guys give me a ride?~ you ask. 
	    ~It's real important.~^^The most intelligent of them -- 
	    maybe just because he wears glasses and doesn't have any 
	    overtly marijuana-oriented garments on -- fixes with you 
	    a look. ~Sorry, man, we got a ride from Wanda.~";

	 Smell:
	    "You hate the smell of pot, never understood exactly 
	    why.";
	],
	each_turn
	[;
	    if (random(4) == 1)
		switch (random(11))
		{
		 1, 2, 3, 4, 5:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " stretches a 
			little and yawns.";

		 6:
		    "^~Dude, do you know where the Triscuits went?~
		    the stoner on the left asks.^^~No,~ the one on the
		    right says after some thought.^^~How fucking sad
		    is that... reduced to fucking Triscuits,~ the left
		    one replies.";

		 7:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " laughs for 
			no discernable reason.";

		 8:
		    print_ret "^~Dude, I love this part,~ one of ",
			(the) self, " comments. ~You'd never think 
			Dr. Who was such a lush.~";

		 9:
		    print_ret "^~I'm bored,~ one of ", (the) self, " 
			says. The rest murmur agreement.";

		 10:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " belches. ~My 
			bad,~ he says.";

		 11:
		    print_ret "^One of ", (the) self, " punches the 
			one next to him. ~Why'd you do that?~ he 
			asks.^^~Saturdays just make me feel 
			violent.~";
		};
	],
	drug_check
	[;
	    if (self.number == 3)
		"^~Why are you asking us all these questions, man?
		Do we look like a drug reference to you?~ the one on
		the right interjects.^^~Kinda, yeah,~ you
		reply.^^~Well, alright,~ he says.";
	],
	talked_wanda false,
	talked_sue false,
	asked_ride false,
	number 0,
 has 	animate pluralname male concealed;

PartyRoom kitchen "Kitchen"
 with 	description
	    "An island of calm and fluorescence. The music is just 
	    muffled enough by the walls that you can't hear any of 
	    the words -- instead it's a steady humdrum. The 
	    kitchen's the usual first-apartment affair: aging white 
	    tile floor, 60's era cabinets. A dishwasher, maybe still 
	    functional beyond its design life, and a refrigerator 
	    humming softly. There's not much decor beyond the series 
	    of photographs of drunk people, love letters, and 
	    past-due notices stuck on the fridge.^^To the south is 
	    the foyer.",
	s_to foyer;

Object 	-> kitchen_cabinets "cabinets"
 with 	name
	    'cabinet' 'cabinets',
	description
	    "They're made of lacquered dark brown wood -- dunno
	    which kind. You've never been much of an expert on
	    lumber.",
	before
	    [;
	     Open:
		<<Search self>>;
		
	     Search:
		give self open;
		print "A quick search of ", (the) self, " reveals an 
		    unexciting collection of food: sugar, flour, 
		    salt... three boxes of fettucini";
		
		if (flashlight in self)
		{
		    "... oh hey, look, there's a flashlight in
		    here. Why do people keep emergency supplies in
		    their kitchen, anyway? You do it too, but thinking
		    over it now, it doesn't really make sense.";
		}
		else
		    ".";

	     Receive:
		"Nah, there's no need to start leaving behind presents
		for the party hosts.";
	    ],
 has 	scenery container openable pluralname;

Object	-> -> flashlight "flashlight"
 with 	name
	    'flashlight' 'light' 'torch' 'slider' 'switch' 'plastic',
	description
	[;
	    print "It's an average-sized plastic one, with a fat
		slider switch for easy lighting action. Right now,
		it's ";
	    if (self has on)
		"on.";
	    else
		"off.";
	],
	after
	[;
	 SwitchOn:
	    ! If we are in a dark location, look again
	    
	    give self light;
	    print "You click ", (the) self, " on.^";

	    if ((location ofclass DarkenedRoom) ||
		(location == waiting_room))
	     	<<Look>>;
	    else
		rtrue;

	 SwitchOff:
	    give self ~light;
	    print_ret "You click ", (the) self, " off.";
	],
 has	switchable;

Object 	-> -> kitchen_cabinets_food "food"
 with	name
	    'sugar' 'salt' 'flour' 'fettucini' 'box' 'boxes' 'three'
	    '3//' 'two' '2//' 'one' '1//' 'food' 'pasta',
	description
	    "Pretty much what you'd expect.",
	before
	[;
	    if (action ~= ##Examine)
		"You weren't planning to do any cooking tonight if 
		it could be at all avoided, honestly. Stir fry is 
		kind of the limit of your abilities.";
	];

Object -> kitchen_counters "counters"
 with 	name
	    'counter' 'counters' 'formica',
	description
	[;
	    print "Formica in all its glory";

	    if (children(self))
	    {
		print ". Sitting on the counter is ";
		WriteListFrom(child(self), ENGLISH_BIT);
 	    };
	    
	    ".";
	],
	after
	[;
	 Receive:
	    "Sure, okay, why not?";
	],
 has 	scenery supporter;

Object 	-> kitchen_dishwasher "dishwasher"
 with 	name
	    'dishwasher',
	description
	    "You know, the usual kind that you don't normally pay
	    attention to.",
	before
	[;    
	 Open, Search:
	    "You've always made a rule to stay the hell away from
	    dishwashers at parties whenever possible. Maybe someday
	    you'll miss out some fabulous treasure because of it, but
	    let's face it: 99.99% of the time, they're total grimefests.";

	 SwitchOn:
	    "Nah, that wouldn't really do anyone any good.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> kitchen_detritus "random stuff on the fridge"
 with 	name
	    'drunk' 'people' 'photograph' 'photographs' 'photo'
	    'photos' 'love' 'letter' 'letters' 'past' 'due' 'notice'
	    'notices',
	before
	    "Enh, you've kind of already seen it all before.",
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> kitchen_fridge "refrigerator"
 with 	name
	    'refrigerator' 'fridge' 'door',
	describe
	[;
	    print "^The fridge door's open, displaying a depressing
		selection of beer";
	    if (self.others_inside())
	    {
		print " as well as ";
		self.print_others();
	    };
	    ".";
	],
	description
	[;
	    if (self hasnt open)
		"It's that beautiful light brown color old home
		appliances have -- the kind your parents did, and
		maybe their parents before them.";
	    else
		<<Search self>>;
	],
	before
	[;
	 Empty:
	    "That would be kind of rude.";
	],
	after
	[;
	 Open:
	    give self general;
	    give self ~concealed;
	    print "The fridge door opens, revealing a meager 
		selection of beer. Granted, a step above a case of 
		Natty Boh, but still.^";
	    party_alice.appear();
	    rtrue;

	 Close:
	    give self concealed;
	    "You shut the fridge door.";

	 Receive:
	    print_ret "You put ", (the) noun, " in the fridge... for
		safekeeping?";
	    
	 Search:
	    print "Inside, there's a fairly lame assortment of
		beers.";
	    if (self.others_inside())
	    {
		print " For some reason, there's also ";
		self.print_others();
		" inside.";
	    }
	    else
	    	print_ret " ";
	],
	others_inside
	[ i;
	    objectloop (i in self)
		if (~~ i ofclass FridgeBeer)
		    rtrue;
	    rfalse;
	],
	print_others
	[ i;
	    objectloop (i in self)
		if (~~ i ofclass FridgeBeer)
		    give i workflag;
	    WriteListFrom(child(self), ENGLISH_BIT + WORKFLAG_BIT);
	],
 has 	concealed static container openable;

FridgeBeer -> ->;
FridgeBeer -> ->;
FridgeBeer -> ->;

FridgeBeer -> ->
 with 	dont_take true;

Object 	party_alice
 with	short_name
	[;
	    print (string) aliced.believed_name();
	    rtrue;
	],
	parse_name
	[ word i;
	    while (word = NextWord())
	    {
 		if (word == aliced.grammar_name())
		    i++;
		else
		    if (word == aliced.wrong_grammar_name())
		    {
		    	self.wrong_name = true;
		    	i++;
		    }
		    else
			if (word == 'girl' or 'woman')
			{
		    	    if ((aliced.believed_state ~=
				 aliced.UNKNOWN_STATE) && random(2) == 1)
				self.wrong_name = true;
		    	    i++;
			}
			else
			    return i;
	    };

	    return i;
	],
	sync_belief
	[;
	    ! This should be called before any social interaction happens.
	    
	    if (self.wrong_name)
	    {
	    	aliced.sync_belief();
		self.wrong_name = false;
	    	print_ret "~", (string) aliced.wrong_name(), "--~^^~My 
		    name's ", (string) aliced.short_name(), ",~ she 
		    interrupts, ", (string) random("looking kind of 
						   peeved.",
				    		   "grimacing.",
						   "frowning.");
	    };
	],
	initial
	[;
	    print (string) aliced.believed_name(), " stands in front 
		of you, ";
	    
	    if (self.has_answered)
		"looking kind of amused.";
	    else
		"waiting for some kind of coherent answer.";
	],
	description
	[;
	    if (~~ self.looked)
	    {
		self.looked = true;
		"If you weren't feeling creative and/or on drugs, 
		you'd call her pretty. But she's a particular kind 
		of pretty, the kind of pretty girl you always saw in 
		high school but never seemed to find you interesting 
		enough to talk to.^^She's the kind of girl who's got 
		such an awesome body and a genuine smile that she 
		doesn't have to dress up to look good; in fact, it 
		looks kind of good when she doesn't, like it's even 
		more effortless to look good.^^She's got 
		shoulder-length blonde hair, the kind of impromptu 
		hairdo that looks absolutely killer specifically 
		because it looks impromptu, and she's wearing a nice 
		shirt and a a pair of jeans with a patch on the left 
		knee. The patch looks sort of quilt-like, but it's 
		hard to tell exactly -- hey, be careful now. If you 
		stare too long, you're probably going to creep her 
		out.^^She's looking at you with an undisguised 
		grin, which would normally be unnerving. But the 
		particular endorphins running through your body 
		right now are something else entirely.";
	    }
	    else
		"You give her a little look, almost unconsciously. 
		Not even long enough to tell if she looks back.";
	],
	each_turn
	[;
	    switch (-- self.number)
	    {
	     2:
		if (~~ self.has_answered)
		    "^She gives you a bored sort of look... you plan 
		    on answering her question, chief?";

	     1:
		if (self.has_answered)
		    print_ret "^", (string) aliced.believed_name(),
		    	" looks away for a moment, maybe growing a 
			little bored.";
		else
		    print_ret "^", (string) aliced.believed_name(),
 		    	" taps her foot on the floor, waiting for an 
			answer.";
		
	     0:
	    	self.disappear();
	    	if (self.has_answered)
		{
	       	    print "^~Anyway, I gotta run,~ ", (string)
			aliced.believed_name(), " says. ~Catch you 
			    in the dance?~^^~Sure,~ you say";

		    if (self.likes_player)
		     	".^^She starts to walk away, then turns and
		    	stops for a second -- like she's going to say
		    	something important or dramatic, but then she just
		    	lets off a goofy laugh and leaves.";
		    else
			".";
		}
	    	else
		    print_ret "^~Um, okay, I'll, uh, talk to you 
			later,~ ", (string) aliced.believed_name(),
		    	" says. And as she leaves: ~Thanks for 
			answering my question.~^^That girl's 
			probably got a killer sense of humor, once 
			you got to know her.";
	    };
	],
	react_before
	[;
	 Go:
	    if (noun == s_obj)
	    {
		self.disappear();
		if (self.talked())
		{
		    print "~Anyway, I gotta run,~ you say.^^~Later,~ she 
		    says";

		    if (self.likes_player)
			print ", watching you as you go";

		    print ".^^(Maybe you should've said ~Nice 
			meeting you~ or something like that? Stop 
			being such a fucking dweeb. You're supposed 
			to be cool now.)^";
		}
		else
	       	    print "~I gotta go,~ you say. ~It's, um, 
		    important.~^^She gives you a weird look, but at 
		    least you didn't have to give her a primer on 
		    IPv4.^";
	    };
	],
	life
	[ selftalked;
	    
	 Ask:
	    if (self.sync_belief())
		rtrue;
	    
	    selftalked = self.talked();
	    
	    switch (second)
	    {
	     'car', 'ride':
		<<AskForRide self>>;

	     'shirt', 't-shirt', 'my':
		if (selftalked)
		    "~What's so interesting about my shirt, anyway?~
		    you ask.^^~Nothing... exactly,~ she says. ~I just
		    wondered.~";
		else
		    "~Uh... why are you so interested in my shirt?~ 
		    you ask.^^~Dunno,~ she says, ~Why are you trying
		    to dodge the question?~";

	     'party', 'place', 'house', 'here', 'tonight', 'this':
		if (selftalked)
		{
		    self.talked_wanda = true;
		    print_ret "~So how did a stranger like you end 
			up at this party?~ you ask. ~This party is 
			full of people I vaguely know, so it's 
			interesting to actually see someone 
			new.~^^(This is kind of a lie, but let's 
			call it an exaggeration for the sake of 
			conversational interest.)^^~I'm a friend of 
			Wanda,~ ", (string) aliced.believed_name(),
		    	" says.^^~Oh, okay, I used to go to school 
			with her.~^^(This is a total lie.)";
		}
		else
		{
		    self.likes_player = true;
		    "~The real question,~ you say. ~is how you ended 
		    here tonight.~^^~What do you mean?~ she 
		    asks.^^~Hey, cut me some slack here,~ you say. 
		    ~I'm just trying to be polite here and steer the 
		    conversation away from my stupid shirt.~^^She 
		    sort of laughs a little bit, maybe wondering if 
		    you're acting stupid on purpose.";
		};

	     'beer', 'beers', 'alcohol', 'fridge', 'a//':
		if (self.offered_beer)
		    "Dude, you already tried that tactic.";
		
		if (~~ selftalked)
		{
		    self.offered_beer = true;
		    "~Um, before I answer that, you should have a
		    beer,~ you say.^^~What, are you trying to get me
		    drunk?~ she asks.^^~No, I'm just trying to
		    be, uh, considerate.~^^She looks a little dubious.";
		}
		else
		{
		    self.offered_beer = true;
		    self.likes_player = true;
		    "~Can I get you a beer?~ you ask.^^~Yeah, sure,~
		    she says. You grab a beer from the fridge and toss
		    it to her -- she catches it with a smile.";
		};

	     'stoners', 'stoner':
		if (~~ selftalked)
		    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
		else
		    "~Did you run into those stoners in the living room?~
		    you ask.^^~Yeah, they were kind of losers, don't
		    you think?~ she says. ~I don't get why they're here.~";
		
	     'wanda':
		if (~~ selftalked)
		{
		    self.has_answered = false;
		    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
		};
		    
		if (foyer_stoners.talked_wanda || self.talked_wanda)
		{
		    print "~Have you seen ";
		    
		    if (~~ self.talked_wanda)
			print "a girl named ";
		    
		    "Wanda, by the way?~ you ask.^^~No,~ she says. 
		    ~Last I saw her, she was out smoking on the 
		    porch. But that was like an hour ago.~";
		}
		else
		{
		    self.has_answered = false;
		    "Wanda who?";
		};
		
	     'sue':
		if (~~ selftalked)
		{
		    self.has_answered = false;
		    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
		};
		
		"~I'm looking for someone named Sue,~ you 
		say.^^~Sue?~ she says. ~No, I don't know anybody 
		named Sue.~";
		
	     'herself', 'alice', 'alicia', 'girl', 'job', 'work':
		if (selftalked)
		{
		    self.talked_job = true;
		   "~So, like, what do you do?~ you ask.^^~For a
		    living?~ she asks. ~I'm a waitress.~";
		}
		else
		{
		    self.has_answered = false;
	     	    <<Tell self 'myself'>>;
		};

	     'waiting', 'waitress', 'tables', 'waitressing':
		self.likes_player = true;

		if (selftalked || (~~self.talked_job))
		{
		    "~What's waiting tables like?~ you ask.^^~Pretty
		    much how it is in the movies,~ she says. ~Except
		    there's no twist...~";
		}
		else
		    "~Are you a waitress?~ you ask. ~Because you 
		    look like one.~^^She's awestruck for a second, 
		    seems to completely forget her question. ~Yeah 
		    -- yeah, I am,~ she says.";

	     'school', 'college', 'university':
		if (selftalked)
		    "~So, are you like, a college student?~ you 
		    ask.^^~No,~ she says. ~Not anymore. I 
		    graduated...~ Here she pauses to count years on 
		    the ceiling. ~... Five years ago.~";
		else
		    "~Um, are you a college student?~ you ask.^^~Why,
		    am I not going to get it if I'm not?~ she
		    replies.^^~No, uh...~ you trail off.";
		
	     'drug', 'drugs', 'green', 'liquid', 'cough', 'syrup',
	     'bottle':
		self.likes_player = false;
		if (selftalked)
		    "~Forget the t-shirt,~ you say. ~I need your 
		    advice on drugs.~^^She looks pretty unimpressed.";
		else
		    print_ret "~You don't happen to be an expert on 
			drugs at all, do you?~ you ask.^^~What kind 
			of drugs?~", (string) aliced.believed_name(), "
			asks.^^~Well, that's the thing,~ you say. ~I
			don't know what exactly I've gotten myself
			into.~^^~Hmm,~ she says, giving you an odd
			look. ~I probably wouldn't be any help.~";

	     'pole':
		"~Do you know what's up with that pole in the 
		living room?~ you ask.^^~Pole?~ she says. ~I don't 
		know what you mean.~";
		
	     'dance', 'dancing':
		if (~~ selftalked)
		    "~Forget my shirt,~ you say. ~We should be dancing
		    right now.~^^She smiles, unimpressed -- ~";
		else
		{
		    self.disappear();
		    print "~Hey, do you want to dance or something?~
			you ask.^^";
		    if (self.likes_player)
			"~Okay,~ she says. ~I've got to find 
			somebody, but I'll meet you on the dance 
			floor in a minute?~^^~Sounds like a cool 
			plan,~ you say as she gives you a nod and 
			walks out of the kitchen.";
		    else
			"~No thanks,~ she says. ~Anyway, I've gotta
			run.~^^~Uh, see you,~ you say.";
		}
	     default:
		self.number--;
		"~Uh...~ you bravely venture.";
	    	};

	 Tell:
	    if (self.sync_belief())
		rtrue;
	    
	    selftalked = self.talked();
	    
	    switch (second)
	    {
	     'myself', 'me':
		if (selftalked)
		{
		    if (self.talked_name)
		    	print_ret "~Did I mention my name's Dante?~ you 
			    ask.^^~Um, yeah, I caught that,~ ", (string)
			    	aliced.believed_name(), " says.";
		    else
		    {
			self.talked_name = true;
			aliced.sync_belief();
			print_ret "~My name's Dante,~ you say.^^~I'm
			    ", (string) aliced.believed_name(), ",~
			    she says.";
		    };
		}
		else
		{
		    print "~Before I tell you about my shirt, you 
			oughta at least know my name first,~ you 
			say.^^~Do names matter to you?~ she
			asks.^^>>";
		    self.talked_name = true;
		    aliced.sync_belief();
		    
		    if (YesOrNo())
			"~Yeah, they do. I'm Dante,~ you say.^^~I'm 
			Alice,~ she says. Maybe she looks impressed?";
		    else
		    {
			self.likes_player = true;
			"~No, but I'm just trying to avoid a boring 
			discussion of my shirt,~ you say.^^She 
			laughs. A genuine sort of laugh, the kind of 
			thing almost never audible at parties. ~My 
			name is Alice,~ she says.";
		    };
		};
		
	     'shirt', 't-shirt', 'joke', 'geeky', 'geek', 'my',
	     'unix', 'linux', 'localhost':
		if (selftalked)
		    "~Well, the thing about the shirt is it's a joke 
		    based on the way the Internet works... I mean, 
		    like everything has an address and stuff, just 
		    like in real life, so 127.0.0.1~ -- here you 
		    point at your shirt like a dumbass, like she's 
		    illiterate -- ~is the address for the machine 
		    you're on... like, it's your home.~^^~Uh hunh,~ 
		    she says, clearly not really up for IPv4 101.";
		else
		    "~Well, you see, on the Internet, everthing has 
		    an address, right?~^^~Okay,~ she says.^^~So the 
		    addresses are what's called dotted quads, 
		    because they're four numbers separated by 
		    period...~^^Her smile is quickly fading here, 
		    Dante. Do something smart and do it fast. ";
		
	     default:
		<<Ask self 'uh'>>;
	    };
	    
	 Show, Give:
	    if (noun ofclass FridgeBeer)
	    	if (~~ self.offered_beer)
	 	{
		    move noun to self;
		    self.offered_beer = true;
   		    self.likes_player = true;
		    print "~Thanks,~ she says.";

		    if (~~ self.has_answered)
			" ~But you haven't answered my question.~";
		    else
			" ~People aren't usually this nice to 
			me.~^^You shoot her a goofy, earnest smile.";
		}
	    	else
		    "~Nah, I only need one,~ she says.";
	    
	    if (noun == silver_key)
	    {
		aliced.sync_belief();
		"~Weird,~ she says. ~You don't run into too many keys
		with your name on them.~";
	    }
	    else
		print_ret (string) aliced.believed_name(), " gives 
		    it a once-over, but doesn't seem that amazed.";

	 Answer:
	    if (~~ self.talked())
		<<Tell self 'joke'>>;
	    else
		<<Ask self 'uh'>>;
	    
	 Attack:
	    "Wow, that'd be a terrible idea.";

	 Kiss:
	    self.disappear();
	    "She gives you a shove, a serious one, the kind that 
	    cannot be interpreted as anything but: fuck 
	    off.^^~What's your problem?~ she asks, and when you 
	    don't have any kind of ready reply, she disappears into 
	    the living room. ";
	],
	orders
	[;
	    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
	],
	before
	[;
	 AskForRide:
	    if (self.talked())
	    {
		self.disappear();
		print "~Hey, would you mind giving me a ride?~ you 
		    ask.^^", (string) aliced.believed_name(), " 
		    looks at you, weighing things for a second. 
		    ~What, back to your place?~ she asks.^^>>";

		if (YesOrNo())
		    print "~Normally, the answer would be yes,~ you 
			say. ~But I'm on a mission.~";
		else
		    print "~Sorry, but no,~ you say. ~I'm on a 
			mission.~";

		print_ret "^^~A mission,~ she says. ~A mission. For 
		    serious.~^^She looks at you.^^~Can I get a rain 
		    check?~ you ask.^^~Sorry,~ ", (string)
			aliced.believed_name(true), " says. ~I'm not 
			    Super Fresh.~^^She turns and walks away 
			    a little, then adds just as she turns a 
			    corner and disappears from your life 
			    forever: ~I wish sometimes things didn't 
			    happen the way they do.~^^Before you can 
			    agree, she's gone.";
	    }
	    else
	    {
		self.disappear();
		"~Forget my shirt -- I have an important question 
		for you,~ you say.^^~What?~ she asks.^^~Could you 
		give me a ride somewhere?~^^She gives you a cold 
		kind of look.^^~Sorry,~ she says. ~You know that 
		saying about accepting rides from 
		strangers?~^^~Yeah,~ you say, ~But you seem--~^^~I 
		also believe in the reverse,~ she says, and while 
		you're puzzling that one out, she turns around and 
		walks away.^^Ouch.";
	    };
	],
	appear
	[;
	    if (~~ self.has_appeared)
	    {
	    	move self to location;
	    	self.has_appeared = true;
		SetPronoun('her', self);
		self.number = 4;
	    	"^~Hey, what's your shirt mean?~ this girl who 
		apparently has silently queued up nearby in hopes 
		you would sometime get around to opening the 
		fridge.^^~It's a geeky joke,~ you say.^^~Yeah, but 
		what makes it funny?~ She seems to earnest on this 
		point, not trolling you high school style.^^~Uh...~ 
		you say, desperately trying to think of some way to 
		turn this conversation around.";
	    };
	],
	disappear
	[;
	    ! Note that unlike appear(), this prints nothing, because
	    ! we disappear for several different reasons.

	    remove self;
	],
	talked
	[ i;
	    ! This returns whether the player has answered Alice's
	    ! question, but also has the side effect of resetting
	    ! Alice's timer of getting bored and leaving.

	    i = self.has_answered;
	    self.has_answered = true;
	    self.number = 5;
	    return i;
	],
	looked false,
       	wrong_name false,
	likes_player false,
	has_appeared false,
	has_answered false,
	talked_wanda false,
	talked_name false,
	offered_beer false,
	talked_job false,
	number 0,
 has 	animate female;

PreDanceObject predance_music "music"
 with 	name
	    'music' 'sound' 'beat',
	description
	    "You aren't quite cool enough to be able to see sound. At
	    least not yet...",
	before
	[;
	 Listen:
	    print_ret "Listening to ", (the) self, "? Kind of like 
		breathing the air -- you're surrounded by it, almost 
		drowning in it.";
	];

PreDanceObject predance_people "people dancing"
 with 	name
	    'people' 'person' 'dancers' 'dancer' 'crowd' 'dance',
	description
	    "There are faces to look at, and perhaps details of
	    clothes to be noted, but you can't focus on anything
	    long enough to catalog it.",
	before
	[;
	 AskForRide:
	    "It's too loud -- nobody can hear you.";

	 Enter:
	    switch (location)
	    {
	     edge_of_dance:
		<<Go nw_obj>>;

	     standing_in_dance:
		<<Go sw_obj>>;

	     crammed_corner:
		<<Go e_obj>>;
	    };
	],
	life
	[;
	 Ask, Tell, Answer:
	    "It's too loud -- nobody can hear you.";

	 Attack, Kiss, WakeOther, Give, Show:
	    "You can barely catch sight of one person long enough to
	    see them. Forget about any kind of complicated
	    transaction.";
	],
	orders
       	    "It's too loud -- nobody can hear you.",
 has 	animate pluralname;

Object 	predance_pole "pole"
 class 	PredanceObject FarScenery,
 with	name
	    'pole' 'dark' 'shape',
	description
	    "It isn't so much a problem of distance as it is 
	    persistence of vision. Whatever it is, it's about 
	    six-and-a-half feet tall. And you keep catching glimpses 
	    of what looks like clothing: is it a totem pole or 
	    something dressed up a person? It's almost certainly not 
	    a real person. It's too still to be alive.";

PreDanceRoom edge_of_dance "The Edge of the Dance"
 with 	description
	    "The only detail you can seize on is the hardwood floor.
	    This probably once was a regular old living room, with
	    bookcases, an easy chair with the stuffing half missing
	    -- all that good stuff. But now it's all a mess. You
	    can't even count how many people are dancing. Every time
	    you start, people start shifting around and you can't
	    remember whether you'd counted the guy with
	    highlighter-yellow hair already or left him for later.
	    And the pole -- what's up with that pole? It's not
	    exactly a pole. It doesn't reach the ceiling entirely
	    but you can't make out any other detail.^^The music is
	    insane: some Linkin Park shit mixed in with The Flaming
	    Lips and maybe the Beatles' Abbey Road, and whoever it
	    is that's DJing this thing has got it cranked so loud
	    that you can barely float two thoughts in your head at
	    once.^^It looks like there's a slight opening in the
	    crowd to the northwest, and back east is the foyer.",
	e_to foyer,
	nw_to standing_in_dance;

PreDanceRoom standing_in_dance "Standing in the Dance"
 with 	description
	    "Everyone's moving in this weird rhythm that doesn't 
	    seem to have anything to do with the music or any other 
	    system of dance you've read about. But it's fucking cool 
	    to watch. It's like they all know something you don't 
	    and have been practicing since before you were 
	    born.^^There looks like there might be an opening in the 
	    crowd to the southwest, towards the center, where that 
	    pole is.",
	se_to
	    "You turn to try to go back the way you came, but the
	    way is blocked.",
	sw_to
	[;
	    print "You almost get through the opening, but then you
		get crowded out into a corner. It's impossible to
		walk anywhere -- people keep bumping into you, like
		you don't belong.^";
	    return crammed_corner;
	];

PreDanceRoom crammed_corner "Crammed in a Corner"
 with 	description
	    "As far as points of interest go, it's you, a bookcase
	    full of stuff probably nobody in this house has bothered
	    to read, and a small window. There's nothing worse than
	    getting stuck in a corner at any kind of dance -- you
	    always get that odd awkward feeling that you first found
	    in middle school.^^It looks like you might be able to
	    scuttle east, against the wall, to the foyer.",
	e_to foyer;

Object 	-> crammed_corner_bookcase "bookcase"
 with	name
	    'book' 'books' 'case' 'bookcase' 'texts' 'text'
	    'textbooks',
	description
	    "You scan the titles briefly -- nothing really 
	    important. Mostly just leftover college textbooks.",
	before
	[;
	 Push, Pull:
	    "It's too heavy -- and besides, it's pretty doubtful that
	    there's a secret passage behind it.";

	 Receive:
	    "Forget it. It's not worth your time.";

	 Take:
	    "None of the books seem really useful.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> crammed_corner_window "window"
 with	name
	    'window' 'small',
	description
	    "Your eyes flick from rowhouse to rowhouse -- some still
	    lit, some not.",
	before
	[;
	 Open:
	    "There doesn't seem to be any obvious advantage in that.";

	 Close:
	    print_ret (The) self, "'s already closed.";
	],
 has	scenery;

! This next room is kind of weird and very functional. It encompasses
! wherever you'd want to wander while dancing -- there is a virtual
! 5x5 space in which the player moves. Chris/the pole is in the
! center. The player has 9 turns before being swept away by the whole
! thing -- the description property changes to reflect that. The
! player's compass is a bit dodgy (sometimes moving nw instead of n,
! for example) and each move, the player is rotated counter-clockwise
! around the origin.
!
! Note that in this room's mini-coordinate system, (0, 0) is where the
! pole is.

Object dancing_dance "Dancing in the Dance"
 with description
	[;
	    switch (self.number)
	    {
	     9:
	    	print "You can go anywhere you want. You can see
		    anything you want. Where are you? There are five
		    hundred people crammed into this room -- it's a
		    miracle of genetic instinct and secular humanism
		    that no one's bumping into anyone else, except
		    when they want to, which is always... Why don't
		    you touch people more? You never hug people
		    except when they hug you first. Your grandmother
		    leaving for a trip to New Orleans, to see where
		    her body will reside once she's gone up to
		    wherever it is that grandmothers belong after
		    they die...^^";

	     8:
		print "You can hear it all now. You can know
		    everything. You brush hands with someone and for
		    a long descending guitar riff, you have a
		    partner. Who it is -- even male or female, hair
		    color, Alice or Alicia -- you don't know, but
		    what difference does identity make, anyway? Just
		    be cool for once in your life. Just fucking
		    dance. Do you still have a goal in mind here?
		    Maybe you should just stay here all night. Maybe
		    this is poisonous and you don't know it, and
		    maybe you shouldn't care.^^";

	     7:
		print "Wobble the wobble. Sing the song. How do
		    people write songs? Do the words come first or
		    the melody? Probably it depends...^^";

	     6:
		print "Once there was a boy named you, and one night
		    he awoke with a start because he had forgotten
		    to shut the windows of the house, and all the
		    monsters of the world sneaked in... Jesus
		    Christ, you're freaking out here. Better get
		    somewhere definite before you're gibbering like
		    a children's book author.^^";
		
	     5:
		print "You can barely move now -- no, you can barely
		    think. Your brain is changing, you think, but
		    it's just the heat. Why is it so hot? It's
		    April, isn't it?^^";

	     4:
		print "You find yourself for the briefest moment
		    face to face with someone else -- maybe only
		    inches separating the two of you. But then
		    they're gone, and you can't remember a thing, so
		    maybe they were never there at all. Maybe you
		    are dreaming.^^";
		
	     3:
		print "This doesn't feel right at all. Something's
		    wrong. Something's really wrong and you keep
		    dancing.^^";
	     2:
		print "Lost lost lost lost lost lost.^^";

	     1:
		print "Dance dance dance dance dance dance.^^";
	    };

	    self.describe_pole();
	],
	before
	[ direction_changed;
	 StopDancing:
	    print "Plant two feet solidly on the ground, don't even
		bother with that stupid head bop you always find
		yourself doing -- easy as that, the crowd guides you
		away. There's no time for people like you.^";
	    self.player_x = 4;
	    self.player_y = 2;
	    self.number = 9;
	    PlayerTo(crammed_corner);

	 Dance:
	    "You do it without thinking now, like breathing.";
	    
	 Go:
	    if (noun == u_obj or d_obj)
	    {
		! can't go that way
		L__M(##Go, 2, noun);
		rtrue;
	    };

	    if (noun == in_obj or out_obj)
		"But which way is that?";
	    
	    if (--self.number == 0)
	    {
		deadflag = DEAD_CUBICLE;
	     	"You try to move but find you're lost. You're just
		gone. The music's too much for a weak thin boy like
		yourself.^^Don't feel bad. You never had a chance.
		Don't worry. You wake up in the morning and it's as
		if nothing at all happened to you. You don't even
		remember that Beatrice called you.";
	    };

	    if ((player.beers) && (random(3) == 1))
	    {
		! mutate the direction the player is moving in

		direction_changed = true;
		
	    	switch (noun)
	    	{
	     	 n_obj:
		    noun = random(nw_obj, ne_obj);

	     	 ne_obj:
		    noun = random(n_obj, e_obj);
		    
	     	 e_obj:
		    noun = random(ne_obj, se_obj);
		    
	     	 se_obj:
		    noun = random(e_obj, s_obj);
		    
	     	 s_obj:
		    noun = random(se_obj, sw_obj);

	     	 sw_obj:
		    noun = random(s_obj, w_obj);
		    
	     	 w_obj:
		    noun = random(nw_obj, sw_obj);
		    
	     	 nw_obj:
		    noun = random(n_obj, w_obj);
	    	};
	    };
	    
	    ! now actually move
	    
	    switch (noun)
	    {
	     n_obj, ne_obj, nw_obj:
		self.player_y++;

	     e_obj, ne_obj, se_obj:
		self.player_x++;

    	     s_obj, se_obj, sw_obj:
		self.player_y--;
		
	     w_obj, nw_obj, sw_obj:
		self.player_x--;
	    };

	    ! then the player gets rotated
	    ! I'm trying this out to see if this means wine has more
	    ! of an advantage
	    
! 	    if (player.beers)    
! 	    	if (((self.player_y > 0) && (self.player_x > 0)) ||
! 		    ((self.player_y < 0) && (self.player_x < 0)))
! 		    self.player_x = self.player_x * -1;
! 	    	else
! 	    	    if (((self.player_y > 0) && (self.player_x < 0)) ||
! 		    	((self.player_y < 0) && (self.player_x > 0)))
! 		    	self.player_y = self.player_y * -1;
	    
	    ! clamp coordinates
	    ! we don't clamp positive x -- that's how people can leave
	    
	    if (self.player_y < -5)
		self.player_y = -5;
	    if (self.player_y > 5)
		self.player_y = 5;
	    if (self.player_x < -5)
		self.player_x = -5;

	    ! Are we off the floor?

	    if (self.player_x > 5)
	    {
		self.number = 9;
		self.player_x = 4;
		self.player_y = 2;
		PlayerTo(foyer);
		rtrue;
	    };

	    ! Did we make it to the center?

	    if ((self.player_y == 0) && (self.player_x == 0))
	    {
		print "One final step in the right direction and 
		    you're in a weird pocket at the center of the 
		    crowd. A few square feet of emptiness. It feels 
		    good to be able to breathe.^^The music changes. 
		    No more beat, no more vocals, no more almost 
		    anything. It's just a steady tone -- maybe 
		    synthesized, maybe not. Like the hum of a slot 
		    machine paying out three million dollars.^";
 		PlayerTo(center_dance);
		 rtrue;
	    };

	    if (player.beers)
	    {
	    	print (string) random("You try your best to direct your 
				      groove, ", "You try hard to move 
				      where you need to, ");
	    	print (string) random("but it's like swimming in a pool 
				      full of screaming children.", "but 
				      people push back against you, like 
				      you're their enemy.", "but it's 
				      almost impossible to remember the 
				      path your feet should take.");
	    	if (direction_changed)
		    print ".. plus this beer is fucking you up. Fucking 
		    	cheapass swill.";
	    }
	    else
		print (string) random("You swim through the crowd.",
				      "It's so easy, fitting through 
				      the gaps and spaces and 
				      grooves.");
	    
	    print "^";
	    <<Look>>;
	    
	 Exit:
	    "But which way is out?";
	],
	describe_pole
	[ north east south west;
	    if (self.player_y > 0)
		south = true;
	    
	    if (self.player_y < 0)
		north = true;
	    
	    if (self.player_x > 0)
		west = true;
	    
	    if (self.player_x < 0)
		east = true;
	    
	    print "The pole ";
	    
	    if (self.number == 9)
		print "-- the pole? -- ";
	    
	    print "you had noticed before is ";
	    
	    if ((abs(self.player_y) == 1) || (abs(self.player_x) ==
					      1))
		print "a few feet away, ";
	    else
		if ((abs(self.player_y) <= 3) && (abs(self.player_x)
						  <= 3))
		    print "maybe ten feet away, ";
	    
	     print "to the ";
	    
	    if (north)
	    {
		if (east)
		    print "northeast";
		else
		    if (west)
			print "northwest";
		     else
			 print "north";
	    }
	    else
		if (south)
		{
		    if (east)
			print "southeast";
		    else
			if (west)
			    print "southwest";
			 else
			     print "south";
		}
		else
		    if (east)
			print "east";
		    else
			print "west";
	    
	    ".";
	],
	each_turn
	[ i new_i;
	    
	    ! Clear any dropped items

	    i = child(self);

	    while (i)
	    {
		new_i = sibling(i);
		if (i ~= player or dance_pole or dance_people)
		    remove i;
		i = new_i;
	    };
	    
	    if (self.number > 6)
	    {
		print "^~";

		switch (random(7))
		{
		 1:
	    	    print "Boys forget promises";

		 2:
		    print "I wanna see their faces";

		 3:
		    print "Let's go down the waterfall";

		 4:
		    print "There are 80 windows we can see";

		 5:
		    print "So I'm gonna change -- maybe tonight";

		 6:
		    print "True love is hard to find";
		    
		 7:
		    print "There was no future left at all";
		};

    		",~ a mutated voice sings.";
	    }
	    else
		if (self.number > 3)
		{
		    print "^~";
		    switch (random(5))
		    {
		     1:
			print "You were dreams";
			
		     2:
			print "So leave behind";

		     3:
			print "409";

		     4:
			print "So they didn't make me Saturdays";

		     5:
			print "It wants to be said";
		    };

		    "...~";
		}
	    	else
		{
		    print "^(";
		    switch (random(5))
		    {
		     1:
			print "it's go don't die";

		     2:
			print "every morn I saw";

		     3:
			print "pulling";

		     4:
			print "Dante listen now";

		     5:
			print "and pat you find out";
		    };

		    ")";
		};
	],
	after
	[;
	 Drop:
	    print_ret "As soon as you put it down, ", (the) noun, "'s 
		gone, swept away by the dance.";
	],
	number 9,
	player_x 4,
	player_y 2;

FarScenery -> dance_pole "pole"
 with 	name
	    'pole',
	description
	    "You see parts of its shape but can't assemble it into a
	    whole. It's all confusing. Four fingers? An eye? What is
	    it made out of?";

Object -> dance_people "people"
 with 	name
	    'people' 'person' 'dancing' 'dancers',
	description
	    "Waving arms, thrashing feet, closed eyes.",
	before
	[;
	    if (action ~= ##Examine or ##StopDancing) 
	    	"It's too confusing in here. It's too weird.";
	],
 has 	animate concealed;

Object 	center_dance "At the Center"
 with 	description
	[;
	    if (self hasnt visited)
	    	print "It wasn't a pole at all you were looking at. 
		    What the hell is wrong with you? It's a guy -- 
		    granted, a tall guy who's nearly catatonic.";
	    else
		if (center_dance_chris hasnt proper)
		    print "So here you are at the center of things, 
			face to face with some weirdo.";
	    	else
	       	    print "Chris stands here at the center of 
			things, still lost or confused or something. 
			He doesn't seem that perturbed by the scene 
			around him for some reason.";

	    if (center_dance_chris hasnt proper)
	    	print " His eyes stare straight ahead and his arms 
		    are as limp as a mackerel.";
	    
	    if (self hasnt visited)
   	    	print "^^Everyone else is still dancing, as if they 
		    still hear the music? So maybe it's just you? 
		    Maybe you've gone selectively deaf? Or maybe 
		    they lost their hearing a long time ago, but 
		    they're so used to dancing that they don't even 
		    know that everything is different now?";
	    else
		print " And everyone else is still dancing, as if
		    the music was just as it was, as if there was
		    nothing wrong at all.";
	    
	    "^^You could probably make cut eastward through the
	    crowd, back to the foyer.";
	],
	e_to
	[;
	    print "The moment you step away from him, the music
		resumes. You don't understand, but it's happening,
		everything is happening --^";
	    return foyer;
	],
	before
	[;
	 Dance:
	    "Go back into the fray? It seems like a bad idea.";
	];

Object -> center_dance_chris
 with 	short_name
	[;
	    if (self has proper)
		print "Chris";
	    else
		print "guy";
	    rtrue;
	],
	name
	    'chris' 'guy' 'klimas' 'dude' 'man' 'weirdo',
	description
	    "As previously observed, he's about six-and-a-half feet
	    tall, with blond hair that's pretty much a wreck. Blue
	    eyes, too, sober as the day is long. He has a black
	    T-shirt on, just like you, only it's blank.^^The one
	    weird thing is that he's carrying a book, but the cover
	    doesn't have a title on it or anything.",
	before
	[;
	 Push:
	    if (~~ self.awake)
	    {
		print "You give him a little shove on his shoulder. ";
		self.wake();
		rtrue;
	    }
	    else
		"No need to now. He looks like he's awake.";
	    
	 AskForRide:
	    if (~~ self.awake)
		"He doesn't even blink in response.";
	    else
	    {
		print "~Hey, could you by any chance give me a 
		    ride?~ you ask.^^He looks surprised for a 
		    moment, then smiles. ~Yeah, sure. This party 
		    kind of sucks, anyway.~^";

		if (self hasnt proper)
		{
		    print "^On the way out, he says, ~By the way, my 
			name's Chris.~^";

		    if (pre_attic_dude.told_name)
			print "^Of course it is.^";
		};  
	    };
	    print "[...]";
	    KeyCharPrimitive();
	    ClearScreen();
	    print "^";
	    PlayerTo(driving_to_donuts);
	    rtrue;
	    
	 ThrownAt:
	    print "Bonk! You manage to score a hit on his forehead. ";
	    self.wake();
	    rtrue;
	],
	life
	[;
	 Attack, WakeOther:
	    if (~~ self.awake)
	    {
		print "You give him a little shove on his shoulder. ";
		self.wake();
		rtrue;
	    }
	    else
		"No need to now. He looks like he's awake.";
	    
	 Kiss:
	    "Hmm. Maybe not.";
	    
	 Ask:
	    if (~~ self.awake)
		"He doesn't even blink in response.";
	    else
		switch (second)
		{
		 'ride', 'car':
		    <<AskForRide self>>;
		    
		 'him', 'himself', 'chris':
		    "~Hey, what's your name?~ you ask.^^~Chris,~ he
		    says, and adds, looking around the room, ~Who
		    are all these people?~";
		    
		 'party', 'here':
		    "~How long have you been here?~ you ask.^^~I
		    got here... at eight?~ he says. Of course. He's
		    one of those people who shows up right on time.
		    ~I was in the living room drinking and talking
		    to... somebody...~";
		    
		 'house':
		    "~What do you think of this house?~ you
		    ask.^^~It's nice,~ he says. ~Seems a little
		    weird that there's only one bathroom, though.~";
		    
		 'drug', 'drugs', 'green', 'liquid', 'cough', 'syrup',
		 'absinthe', 'dxm':
		    "~Do you know much about drugs?~ you ask.^^~No,
		    not really,~ he says, frowning. ~Sad to say, I
		    never thought they were a good idea.~";

		 'book', 'paperback', 'blue':
		    "";
		    
		 default:
		    "~What?~ he asks.";
		};
	    
	 Tell:
	    if (~~ self.awake)
		"He doesn't even blink in response.";
	    else
		switch (second)
		{
		 'me', 'myself':
		    give self proper;
		    "~My name's Dante,~ you say.^^~Nice to meet 
		    you...~ he replies, still a little out of 
		    sorts.^^ ~I'm Chris.~";

		 'drug', 'drugs', 'green', 'liquid', 'cough',
		 'syrup', 'absinthe', 'dxm':
		    "~I just drank this green liquid which I think 
		    is doing something to my brain,~ you 
		    exposit.^^~Yeah?~ he asks.^^~I'm mentioning this 
		    because I can't drive right now,~ you say.^^He 
		    looks at you a little puzzled, waiting for the 
		    point to be brought home.";

		 'beatrice':
		    "~This friend of mine, Beatrice, is in trouble,
		    man,~ you say.^^He looks at you, really actually
		    concerned. ~Are you going to go help her?~";
		    
		 default:
		    "He doesn't seem to hear you, which is weird.";
		};

	 Answer:
	    <<Ask self 'uh'>>;
	],
	wake
	[;
	    SetPronoun('him', self);
	    self.awake = true;
	    print "He startles awake, like he really has been 
		dreaming all this time.^^~Are you here to rescue 
		me?~ he asks.^^>>";
	    if (YesOrNo())
		"~Yeah,~ you say. ~I'm your Prince
		Charming.~^^~Weird,~ the guy says. ~I always
		thought I'd get rescued by a hot chick,
		myself.~^^~Me too,~ you admit.";
	    else
		"~No, man,~ you say. ~I'm not really the
		rescuing type.~^^~Oh,~ he says, sort of like
		he's just been informed that the sky is blue.
		~Well, thanks anyway.~";
	],
	name_known false,
	awake false,
 has 	animate concealed transparent;

Object 	-> -> center_dance_chris_book "blue book"
 with 	name
	    'book' 'blue' 'paperback' 'trendy',
	description
	    "It's a blue paperback with rough edges -- you know, the
	    trendy kind that try to look like they weren't produced
	    in a factory. Beyond that, you can't tell.",
	before
	[;
	 Take:
	    if (~~ center_dance_chris.awake)
	       	print_ret (The) center_dance_chris, " has a solid
		    grip on it.";
	];

!
! Outside
!

Object 	party_street "street"
 with	name
	    'street' 'road' 'cracked' 'torn' 'up' 'torn-up',
	description
	    "The street is cracked, torn-up.",
	before
	[;
	 Enter:
	    "But where do you want to go?";
	],
	found_in front_porch outside_party beside_car, 
 has 	scenery;

Object 	front_porch "Front Porch"
 with 	description
	[;
	    print "You love night breezes. It's hard to say why 
		exactly they make you feel as though as something is 
		changing -- swiftly, invisibly -- about the whole 
		world. As though you could fly, but only as long as 
		you could see the moon.^^The porch is built maybe 
		ten feet above ground, and through some weird 
		configuration of architecture, the night breeze is 
		stronger than you've ever remembered it. Not like a 
		real wind or anything. Just... constant.";

	    if (self hasnt general)
		{
		give self general;
		print " Jesus. Things were getting weird in there. It 
		    was too hot in there. Unnaturally hot. Something 
		    isn't right about that place.";
	    };
	    
	    print "^^";
	    
	    front_porch_guy.print_self();
	    
	    " Downward is the street, and the front door is north.";
	],
	n_to front_porch_door,
	s_to outside_party,
	d_to outside_party,
	in_to
	[;
	    <<Go n_obj>>;
	];

Object 	-> front_porch_chair "lawn chair"
 with 	name
	    'chair' 'lawn',
	description
	    "Looks like the standard issue kind of thing -- probably 
	    glommed from somebody else's basement a long time ago.",
	before
	[;
	 Take:
	    "Mm, no.";
	    
	 Enter:
	    "The passed-out guy's kind of using it right now.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> front_porch_door "front door"
 with 	name
	    'front' 'door' 'blue',
	describe
	[;
	    rtrue;
	],
	description
	    "It's a dull blue color, without any kind of decoration 
	    beyond the house number: 1028.",
	door_dir n_to,
	door_to foyer,
 has 	static door open openable;

Object 	-> front_porch_guy "passed-out guy"
 with 	name
	    'passed' 'out' 'unconscious' 'guy' 'man' 'dude',
	print_self
	[;
	    ! I am doing this in a weird custom method because neither
	    ! describe nor initial will let me output where I want to,
	    ! and I want to keep code where it belongs.
	    
	    print "There's a guy passed out in a lawn chair";
	    
	    if (photograph in self)
		print ", a photograph clutched to his chest";
	    
	    print ", snoring as peacefully as a dog.";
	],
	description
	[;
	    if (photograph in self)
		"He's forty years old, which is sort of weird. Most
		everybody else you've seen here has been in their
		twenties, same as you. And more than being old, he's
		downright scruffy: wife beaters matched with a
		goatee that belongs to a different, uglier place
		than 2004.";
	    else
		"Well, if you allow for about twelve years of fast
		food and a terminally shitty job, he does look like
		he once was the guy in the photo he was holding.
		Damn. So the question is: why was he toting that
		thing around?";
	],
	before
	[;
	 AskForRide:
	    "~Hey, uh, can you give me a ride?~ you ask him, to which
	    he snores a little differently.";

	 ThrownAt:
	    "Wife beaters on a man say many things. One of them in
	    particular is: don't throw shit at me when I'm asleep.";
	],
	life
	[;
	 WakeOther:
	    if (photograph in self)
		"He doesn't stir.";
	    else
		"Right, first steal from him and then wake him up?";

	 Attack:
	    "You give him a little shove, but this guy is out for 
	    the count.";

	 Kiss:
	    "No thanks.";

	 Show:
	    "Hmm, he doesn't seem like he's going to be all that 
	    great of an audience.";

	 Give:
	    if (noun == photograph)
		"You try to thread the photo back into his fingers,
		but it doesn't work.";
	    else
		"You don't think he'd really appreciate it.";

	 Ask, Tell:
	    "No offense, dude, but the guy is sound asleep.";
	],
	orders
	[;
	    "He's asleep, man.";
	],
	each_turn
	[;
	    if (random(2) == 1)
		"^~Zzzzzz,~ the guy snores.";
	],
 has 	animate concealed transparent;

Object 	-> -> photograph "photograph"
 with 	name
	    'photo' 'photograph',
	description
	[;
	    if (self in front_porch_guy)
		"Between the guy's fingers, you can see a young man
		-- not quite enough of his face to be sure if you've
		seen him before. Maybe posed behind a mountain of
		some kind? Maybe smiling?";
	    
	    if (self hasnt general)
	    {
		give self general;
		move photograph to parent(player);
		print_ret (The) self, " is of you.^^It falls to the 
		    ground.";
	    }
	    else
		"You were wrong. It's just someone who looks a lot
		like you -- a little thinner, honestly, and a tad
		better looking. He's standing in front of some kind
		of tropical forest, you know, the kind of thing
		you'd expect out of South America.";
	],
	before
	[;
	 Take:
	    if (self in front_porch_guy)
	    {
		move self to player;
		"With a little deftness, it's yours. You've always 
		wanted to do something like that... even though you 
		feel a bit like a bastard for stealing a fucking 
		photograph, of all things. Too bad it isn't a prison 
		key or something else instead.";
	    };
	];

Object 	outside_party "Standing By the Street"
 with 	description
	    [;
		print "The rowhouses up and down the block are lit
		    up with people and noise, maybe even with
		    parties just like the one you were just in. So
		    many people. It's kind of weird if you think
		    about it for too long. Are they all dancing? Are
		    they all in love? Is there somebody like you,
		    who doesn't really know why they've wandered out
		    here? Maybe hoping for someone random to enter
		    their lives and give them a ride?^^Fuck it.
		    It's a city block, just like any other in
		    Baltimore. Your ";

		if (beside_car_dante_car hasnt general)
 		    print "parked";
		else
		    print "smoking wreck of a";

		" car is a little bit down to the east, and the
		porch steps lead up, back to the house.";
	    ],
	cant_go
	    "It probably would be a bad idea to start wandering 
	    around the city in your state.",
	u_to front_porch,
	n_to front_porch,
	e_to beside_car;

Object 	-> outside_party_houses "rowhouses"
 with 	name
	    'rowhouse' 'rowhouses' 'house' 'houses',
	description
	    "They're crowded against each other like paperbacks in a
	    bookcase.",
	before
	[;
	 Enter:
	    "No need to start canvassing the neighborhood.";
	],
 has 	pluralname scenery;

Object 	beside_car "Beside Your Car"
 with 	description
	[;
	    print "Your beautiful blue Camry ('92, before they got
		sleek and cool) is";
	    
	    if (beside_car_dante_car hasnt general)
		print " hemmed in by a crusty pickup truck in front 
		    of it and a Volkswagen Beetle ('99, sparkly and 
		    new) behind. Well, not really hemmed in. It's 
		    just going to take about five years to get your 
		    car out from the two-inch margin these cars have 
		    left you. Dammit.";
	    else
		print " not looking too great overall, all things 
		    considered. Mostly the part where you rammed it 
		    into a fucking telephone pole. How cliche. If 
		    only you had had to foresight to locate 
		    something new and interesting, say a dumpster 
		    full of gold doubloons, while you were tripping. 
		    Fuck. It's going to cost a serious amount of 
		    money to fix this.";

	    "^^The party is back to the west.";
	],
	w_to outside_party;

Object 	-> beside_car_dante_car "Camry"
 with 	article "your",
	name
	    'car' 'blue' 'camry' 'beautiful' 'vehicle' 'door' 'doors'
	    'toyota',
	description
	[;
	    if (self hasnt general)
	    	"Well, it's not really that beautiful when you look 
		at it somewhat objectively. It came with a slew of 
		dings -- you bought it from an Israeli couple who 
		obviously had personal issues with common household 
		obstacles -- and you've only made the situation 
		worse. Still, it at least gets decent mileage.";
	    else
		"What a wreck.";
	],
	before
	[;
	 Enter, Open:
	    if (self has general)
		"Dude, it's not going anywhere.";
	    
       	    give self general;
	    remove beside_car_pickup_truck;
	    remove beside_car_volkswagon;
	    move beside_car_telephone_pole to location;
	    
	    print "You fumble with your car keys for a second, then 
		open the door.^[...]";
	    KeyCharPrimitive();
	    ClearScreen();
	    print "^";
	    PlayerTo(cruising_baltimore);
	    rtrue;
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> beside_car_pickup_truck "pickup truck"
 with 	name
	    'pickup' 'truck' 'car' 'door' 'doors' 'vehicle' 'crusty',
	description
	    "These fucking dirty rusty things are everywhere, it seems
	    like. This one's owner has decide to flaunt his uniqueness
	    with BUSH/CHENEY 2000 bumper stickers and Calvin pissing
	    on the Dallas Cowboys. Haven't these people heard of
	    intellectual property?",
	before
	[;
	 Enter:
	    "The truck's doors are locked.";

	 Open:
	    <<Enter self>>;
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> beside_car_volkswagon "Volkswagen"
 with 	name
	    'volkswagen' 'volkswagon' 'beetle' 'sparkly' 'new' 'car'
	    'door' 'doors' 'vehicle',
	description
	    "True, you'd never buy one. But you can sort of admire
	    the kind of person who would. It's a statement one way
	    or the other... about something.",
	before
	[;
	 Enter:
	    print_ret (The) self, "'s doors are locked.";

	 Open:
	    <<Enter self>>;
	],
 has 	scenery;

Object 	-> beside_car_telephone_pole "telephone pole"
 with	name
	    'telephone' 'pole' 'wood',
	description
	    "Pretty much everything you could hope for in a 
	    telephone pole.",
	before
	[;
	 Attack, Pull, Push:
	    "You give it a solid kick, which changes approximately 
	    nothing about your situation.";
	],
 has 	scenery;

!
! The title sequence
!


BlueCard title1
 with	text
	    "It seems like now would be an excellent time"
	    "to reflect on why you, once a consistently"
	    "above-average student full of ambition and love,"
	    "just bought an unknown but almost certainly"
	    "illegal substance from a stranger"
	    "and drank it without a second thought.",
	sub_text
	    "k metal" "diment?" "~No mor" "eppermi" "Mr. Pre";

BlueCard title2
 with	text
	    "It would be nice if there were a single moment"
	    "you could use in the event of autobiography"
	    "that would illustrate what happened to you."
	    "Why you feel listless during the day and"
	    "stay up till two in the morning most nights.",
	sub_text
	    "cold ai" "'s no d" "a Chine" "ing gas" "oddy pa";

BlueCard title3
 with	text
    	    "The truth is, there's no story to be told."
	    "It just happened, one second at a time,"
	    " and now you just have to live with it.",
	sub_text
	    "ese cha" "ore 'em" "Se@~nor B" "all rec" "uck Fuc";

BlueCard title4
 with	text
	    "Blue Chairs"
	    "a chance to change"
	    "a story by Chris Klimas",
	sub_text
	    "~Hey ma" "Dante?~" "a voice" "is aski" "or name";

[ Title;
    print "The transaction happens quickly: no hesitations, no 
	reconsiderations, no refunds.^^~Drink it slowly,~ the guy 
	advises but you're already shotgunning it, staring directly 
	at the poor light bulb, so dim it won't even leave behind an 
	afterimage on your retinas, so far away now that the sound 
	of the party below takes five minutes to reach you, so far 
	now that the world is turning blue as it recedes into the 
	distance, so dim now that the wires in the bulb... what are 
	they called?^^Luminants? No, that isn't the right word, 
	that's not even a word at all --^[...]";

    KeyCharPrimitive();
    title1.display();
    title2.display();
    title3.display();
    title4.display();
    
    font on;
    PhoneConversation();
];

[ PhoneConversation;
    font on;
    style roman;
    
    print "^^~Hey man, is your name Dante?~ a voice is asking.^^You
	sit up with a start. ~Yeah.~^^The attic is different now but
	you couldn't say why. How. You don't know how it's
	different. You're sitting on the floor -- lying on it, more
	accurately -- and for a split second, everything's slowed
	down and peaceful and makes sense, even the Easy-Bake
	oven.^^Then this guy with a dirty baseball cap (what the
	fuck? how cliched are we going to get tonight?) who's been
	standing over you has to start talking to you again and it
	fucks everything up. No sign of your esteemed drug merchant,
	of course. He's probably onto bigger and better
	prey.^^~There's this girl who's been calling everyone's cell
	phones asking for you, man.~^^You frown.^^~Here, talk to
	her, man, she's been freaking out on me the last fifteen
	minutes.~^^He presses his cell phone up to your ear, which
	is a nice thing to do considering your arms are completely
	numb for reasons you don't want to think about right
	now.^^~Dante?~ asks a voice you recognize in an instant,
	never mind the cell phone, never mind the years: it's
	Beatrice. If this were a movie, there'd be a convenient fade
	to black to allow you to reminisce about your shared past
	history, perhaps beginning with that sunrise six years ago
	-- but this isn't a movie, kiddo, and she says
	again:^^~Dante, is that you?~^^She's crying.^^";
    PhoneInput();
    print "You try to speak but the words come out all nonsense.
	Isn't that the final insult? Finally a cell phone
	conversation worth having and you can't even form a single
	damn word.^^~Dante, I'm in trouble,~ she says.^^";
    PhoneInput();
    print "You try hard to enuniciate, to make sense, to at least
	convey some mixture of longing and surprise in your tone of
	voice, but you can't do it right.^^~I... I can't explain it
	to you on the phone. But I need you to come help me. Do you
	remember where my house is?~^^";
    PhoneInput();
    print "Of course you remember where her fucking house is. You
	still remember every single thing about her. French toast
	for breakfast with enough syrup to drown yourself...^^~It's
	important,~ Beatrice says. ~Come as soon as you can.~^^
	There's a faint click, like a bird's beak tapping on a
	chalkboard, and then she isn't there anymore.^^Your arms are
	working now -- you're pushing yourself up off the floor
	without even realizing it -- and so is your voice. ~I've got
	to go see her,~ you're saying.^^The guy with the cell phone
	gives you as serious a look as a frat boy can. ~Dude, I've
	never met you before or anything, but can I give you some
	advice? If I were you, I wouldn't drive anywhere tonight?
	Not with the kind of pupils you've got.~^^He backs away from
	you, maybe waiting for a rebuttal. But there's no point in
	arguing with a frat boy who's managed to cobble together
	some kind of personal belief.^^~Can you give me a ride?~ you
	ask.^^~Nah, man,~ he says, suddenly displaying an interest
	in the stairway. ~I gotta get back downstairs. The dance
	won't dance itself, you know what I'm saying?~^^If you were
	not at all on drugs right now, you'd be able to come up with
	a really killer line, but it doesn't matter. There's got to
	be somebody at this hoedown that can get you to Beatrice.^";
    move drug_bottle to player;
    remove green_drugs;
    PlayerTo(post_attic); ];

[ PhoneInput i stop;
    print ">>";
    stop = false;

    while (~~ stop)
    {
	i = KeyCharPrimitive();

	! see the ZSCII chart for the meaning of these numbers

	if (i == 13)
	    stop = true;
	else
	    if (i == 8)
	    	@sound_effect 2;
	else
	    if (((i >= 32) && (i <= 47)) ||
		((i >= 58) && (i <= 64)) ||
		((i >= 91) && (i <= 96)) ||
		((i >= 123) && (i <= 126)))
		print (char) i;
	    else
		print "u";
    };
    print "^";
];
